local_database is used to generate qlocale data from the Common Locale Data Repository (The database for localized names (like date formats, country names etc)).

Download the CLDR core.zip database from http://unicode.org/Public/cldr/ and extract it somewhere convenient.

To convert the CLDR xml database into QLocale xml format run:

  cldr2qlocalexml.py <path/to/cldr/common/main> >> qtlocale.xml

To convet QLocale xml file into C++ encoded look-up tables:

  qlocalexml2cpp.py <path/to/qtlocale.xml> <path/to/qtbase>
